#: ../../M/machoflops.rst:9
msgid ""
"[pun on megaflops, a coinage for ‘millions of FLoating-point Operations Per "
"Second’] Refers to artificially inflated performance figures often quoted by"
" computer manufacturers. Real applications are lucky to get half the quoted "
"speed. See :ref:`Your-mileage-may-vary`\\, :ref:`benchmark`\\."
msgstr ""
"[‘millions of FLoating-point Operations Per "
"Second(毎秒百万浮動小数点演算)’の造語であるmegaflopsのもじり]コンピュータメーカーがしばしば引用する人為的に水増しされた性能数値を指す。実際のアプリケーションは引用された速度の半分でも出れば運がいい。\\"
" :ref:`Your-mileage-may-vary`\\ 、\\ :ref:`benchmark`\\ を参照。"
